A little bit about myself...

My name is Kenneth Petiote and I am a full-time IT Professional.

My knack for learning about technology has lead me to pursuit a certification in Web Development. As an aspiring Developer, I enrolled and completed an extensive Full Stack Web Development Program at Rutgers's Coding Bootcamp.



During the program I have newly acquired skills in HTML, CSS, JavaScript, JQuery, Node.JS, BootStrap, React.js, responsive web design, and Third Party API's; I look forward to writing and developing user-friendly applications and software. Possessing a solid work ethic, excellent communication skills, I am a strong team player who can work within any department as well as independently. I am comfortable with both Agile and Waterfall methodology as well as being Six Sigma Yellow belt and Scrum Master certified.

I love to learn new things, reading, cooking and spending time outdoors. I am a competitve powerlifter, bodybuilder and strength coach.
